{"word":"ἀξιόχρεως","slug":"ἀξιόχρεως","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀξιόχρεως</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:χρέος'><el>χρέος</el></a>\n<p/><i>worthy of a thing</i>, and so,<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, like <el>ἀξιόλογος</el>, <i>note-worthy, considerable, notable</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>serviceable, sufficient</i>, <el>αἰτίη</el> <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>; <el>ἀξ. ἐγγυηταί</el> <i>trustworthy, substantial</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>able, sufficient to</i> do, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> rei, <i>worthy, deserving of</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}